# `shekyl-wallet-state` zeroize-field allowlist
#
# Format: `<relative-path>|<normalized field decl>`, one entry per line.
# Comments start with `#`; blank lines are ignored. `<normalized field
# decl>` is the source line with leading whitespace and a trailing
# comma stripped (matching what `scripts/ci/check_zeroize.sh`
# produces). Entry order is file-alphabetic, declaration-order within
# each file, so diffs against the allowlist read naturally.
#
# Every entry below is a **deliberate public-bytes** field. Either the
# bytes carry no secret material (block hashes, tx hashes, key images,
# published public keys), or the field is a mirror-struct shadow that
# exists only to drive `postcard_schema::Schema` derivation and never
# allocates at runtime, or the field lives in `ledger_indexes.rs` which
# is rebuilt in memory on every load and never persisted.
#
# If you are **adding** a new unwrapped field, stop and decide:
#
#   - Is it a secret? If yes, wrap it in `Zeroizing<...>` (or a typed
#     secret wrapper over `Zeroizing<T>`). No allowlist entry needed.
#   - Is it genuinely public bytes? Add an entry here with a
#     justification in the preceding `#` comment.
#
# If you are **removing** a field whose entry appears below, also
# remove the allowlist line in the same commit. A stale entry is a
# CI-blocking error — it would silently permit a future field with
# the same spelling to land unwrapped.
#
# Policy:
#   .cursor/rules/42-serialization-policy.mdc
#   docs/MID_REWIRE_HARDENING.md §3.5

# ── bookkeeping_block.rs ──────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Subaddress registry keys its entries by the 32-byte pubkey hash that
# the address-derivation pipeline emits for a given subaddress. Public
# by construction — the wallet file's bookkeeping block is the index of
# how pubkey-hash → (major, minor) subaddress index. No secret.
rust/shekyl-wallet-state/src/bookkeeping_block.rs|pub subaddress_registry: BTreeMap<[u8; 32], SubaddressIndex>

# ── ledger_block.rs ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Blockchain tip hash is the 32-byte block hash the wallet last saw.
# Published in every mined block header; no secret.
rust/shekyl-wallet-state/src/ledger_block.rs|pub tip_hash: Option<[u8; 32]>
# Reorg trail is the height-plus-block-hash tuple sequence used to
# detect reorgs at scan time. Block hashes are public network state.
rust/shekyl-wallet-state/src/ledger_block.rs|pub blocks: Vec<(u64, [u8; 32])>

# ── payment_id.rs ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Clear payment ID bytes. The on-wire form is XOR-obfuscated against a
# shared secret before it lands in a tx, but the `PaymentId` type
# itself holds the 8-byte clear value as a public handle — the obfu-
# scation is applied separately by the tx-builder.
rust/shekyl-wallet-state/src/payment_id.rs|pub struct PaymentId(pub [u8; 8]);

# ── ledger_indexes.rs ────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Runtime indexes are rebuilt from `LedgerBlock::transfers` on every
# wallet load; they are never serialized to disk (`LedgerIndexes` has
# no `Serialize` / `Deserialize` derive). Map-key types here (`[u8; 32]`
# key-image bytes, `[u8; 32]` output-pubkey bytes) are all public by
# construction: key images are the public spent-marker primitives,
# output pubkeys are what appears in tx outputs on-chain. See
# `docs/V3_WALLET_DECISION_LOG.md` *"`RuntimeWalletState` audit"*
# (2026-04-25) for the runtime-only invariant rationale.
rust/shekyl-wallet-state/src/ledger_indexes.rs|pub(crate) key_images: HashMap<[u8; 32], usize>
rust/shekyl-wallet-state/src/ledger_indexes.rs|pub(crate) pub_keys: HashMap<[u8; 32], usize>

# ── sync_state_block.rs ───────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Creation-anchor hash is the 32-byte block hash at wallet creation
# time — published chain state, public.
rust/shekyl-wallet-state/src/sync_state_block.rs|pub creation_anchor_hash: Option<[u8; 32]>
# Pending tx hashes are 32-byte identifiers of txs the wallet has
# published but not yet seen mined. Tx hashes are public by design
# (they are the primary lookup key into the mempool + chain).
rust/shekyl-wallet-state/src/sync_state_block.rs|pub pending_tx_hashes: Vec<[u8; 32]>

# ── transfer.rs ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# FCMP++ precomputed-path reference block is the block hash the path
# was computed against — public chain state.
rust/shekyl-wallet-state/src/transfer.rs|pub reference_block: [u8; 32]
# `path_blob` holds the serialized FCMP++ precomputed path (opaque
# merkle-proof bytes). The proof is a public-input artifact of the
# full-chain-membership argument; it does not carry private scalar
# material. Leaks the chosen anonymity-set positions but not the
# spender's secrets.
rust/shekyl-wallet-state/src/transfer.rs|pub path_blob: Vec<u8>
# TransferDetails.tx_hash is the 32-byte hash of the tx this output
# lives in. Public network-level identifier.
rust/shekyl-wallet-state/src/transfer.rs|pub tx_hash: [u8; 32]
# TransferDetails.key_image is the published spent-marker when this
# output has been spent. Key images are public by design — that is
# what makes double-spend detection possible.
rust/shekyl-wallet-state/src/transfer.rs|pub key_image: Option<[u8; 32]>

# Mirror-struct `TransferDetailsSchema` — compile-only shadow that
